
You type → bot fills the answer → continues.

---

## 4. Pagination Logic (Unbreakable)
LinkedIn changes their UI often, so this script checks for all:

- `button[aria-label="Next"]`
- Chevron right icon
- Next text button

If any exist → bot advances.  
If none exist → job search completed.

---

## 5. CSV Logging
Each job logs:

| Platform | Search Term | Job Title | Company | Location | Status | Notes |
|----------|-------------|-----------|---------|----------|--------|-------|

Status values:
- `Applied`
- `Skipped`
- `Failed`

---

## 6. Timing Algorithm
To avoid rate-limits:
- Random waits 25–45 sec between job attempts
- Scroll events added to force lazy-load of listings
- Modal close logic bulletproofed

---

## 7. Error Handling
Bot collects:
- Page failure screenshots
- CSV error rows
- Automatic dismiss of broken forms

---

